.Dd April 19, 1991
.Dt STRDUP 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm strdup
.Nd save a copy of a string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <string.h>
.Ft char *
.Fn strdup "const char *str"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn strdup
function
allocates sufficient memory for a copy
of the string
.Fa str ,
does the copy, and returns a pointer to it.
The pointer may subsequently be used as an
argument to the function
.Xr free 3 .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr calloc 3
.Xr malloc 3
.Xr realloc 3
.Xr free 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn strdup
function
.Ud .
